reviews.review_text:
good sounding MONO recording ? one mic ?  was it a stereo mic ?
recording sounds mono...but none the less, it sounds excellent !

best sounding '69 AUD tape I can remember hearing.
Gift From God This little dataset is the best sounding AUD I've ever heard from 1969.

mix when comparing to deadbase, this appears to be a composite of the three nights.  "hurts me too" is a little more mysterious, not appearing in deadbase at the thelma at all (it does pop up on the fillmore 12/05/69, and others obviously).  that doesn't mean they didn't play it, but it could also mean that this is from a different show.  hmmm . . .

sound is awesome!  sure wish there was a complete collection of this aud from all three nights.  i'd almost take it over the board for its ambient ambiance.  very warm sound.

thanks for the upload!
GREAT AUD!!! All I have to say is Bach and Dark Star in one night or one compilation. Either way amazing quality. Its worth the download or stream.
stereo version? navajo, you see it anywhere? like bt.etree?
TC says TC says the selection he played at this show on track 5 is French Suite Allemande.  Also, he recalls Stephen Stills sat in at this show.

Yes its mono one non stereo mic Hey it is mono but the mic was on the stage DFC.. There is a stereo ms synthesized version but I only listen to this.. What a document..

We just got a reel from Rion that is a 1st gen of the master of some of the remainder of the show .. stay tuned .. its being baked.. Cryptical I think ;-)
Remarkable sound for 1969 so I will remark. Best sound for a '69 aud that I've heard yet. Show is short but sweet, vintage early Dead. Enjoy! Peace

Ditto To What They Said... The former reviewers...

Definitely a great show -- such as it is.

It is incomplete, though. Oh, well, nun-the-less, swell! 

Takes your ears sum gettin used to.

Amazing rockout version of Dark Star.
